ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service - package ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service
 
calculateDuplicateVersion(TreeManager) - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service.ForecastService
This is a helper method that calculated the version number of the duplicate TreeManager For example, if a forecast on base 1.0 is requested, the duplicate version number is 2.0 This duplicate version is only created for the first forecast of a base.
calculateForecastVersion(TreeManager) - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service.ForecastService
This helper method calculates the version number for a forecast.
copyAllContents(TreeManager, TreeManager) - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service.ForecastService
This method copies all contents from one TreeManager to the next.
createForecast(String, String, int, List<TreeDto>, List<Tree>) - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service.ForecastService
This method creates a forecast given a list of trees to plant and trees to cut down.
cutDownTrees(List<Tree>, TreeManager, TreeManager) - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse321.TreePLE.service.ForecastService
This method is used to cut down trees in the forecast TreeManager version if the user has requested it when creating the forecast
